Package us.ihmc.euclid.referenceFrame.interfaces

Interface FixedFrameVector2DBasics

  • All Superinterfaces:
    us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Clearable, FixedFrameTuple2DBasics, FrameTuple2DReadOnly, FrameVector2DReadOnly, ReferenceFrameHolder, us.ihmc.euclid.interfaces.Transformable, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple2D.interfaces.Tuple2DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple2D.interfaces.Tuple2DReadOnly, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple2D.interfaces.Vector2DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple2D.interfaces.Vector2DReadOnly
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FrameVector2DBasics
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FrameVector2D
    public interface FixedFrameVector2DBasics
extends FrameVector2DReadOnly, FixedFrameTuple2DBasics, us.ihmc.euclid.tuple2D.interfaces.Vector2DBasics
    Write and read interface for a 2D vector expressed in a constant reference frame, i.e. this vector is always expressed in the same reference frame.

    In addition to representing a Vector2DBasics, a ReferenceFrame is associated to a FixedFrameVector2DBasics. This allows, for instance, to enforce, at runtime, that operations on vectors occur in the same coordinate system.

    Because a FixedFrameVector2DBasics extends Vector2DBasics, it is compatible with methods only requiring Vector2DBasics. However, these methods do NOT assert that the operation occur in the proper coordinate system. Use this feature carefully and always prefer using methods requiring FixedFrameVector2DBasics.
